    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-30T03:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-30T03:30:00-05:00" n="356"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AA/3–3051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-30T16:00:00+07:30"
                            >March 30, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1337. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 961. Ref Usgoc 498<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d356fn1">Not printed.</note> and 499. In informal mtg this morning,
                        <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> agreed US proposal namely as follows: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> will address factual,
                            non-controversial report SecGen <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                            developments <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> sovereignty transfer
                            to date incl latest arrangements dispatch remainder ex-<gloss
                                target="#t_KNIL1">KNIL</gloss> to Neth.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Conclusions of report will set forth fol: Mil problems solved with
                            latest agreements on <gloss target="#t_KL1">KL</gloss> and ex-<gloss
                                target="#t_KNIL1">KNIL</gloss> and mil observers to be withdrawn on
                            or before April 6. Since <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> has
                            therefore completed its main task in observing implementation <gloss
                                target="#t_RTC1">RTC</gloss> and since no other foreseeable items to
                            deal with, <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> is adjourning sine
                            die.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> will agree final draft report and
                            conclusions April 2. US and Australian members requested opportunity
                            telegraph conclusions their respective govts for approval.</item>
                        <pb facs="0649" n="631" xml:id="pg_631"/>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item> When finally agreed report will be transmitted SecGen <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> simultaneously Neth High Comm and <gloss
                                target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>. Press release to be issued
                            here announcing <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> decision adjourn
                            sine die and mentioning report being forwarded to above addressees. In
                            meantime <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> agreed keep its decision
                            confidential pending finalization report and communication to parties of
                            above.</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> SecGen Romanos expressed view
                            Secretariat rep must probably remain Djakarta but in view prospective
                                <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> inactivity he hoped <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> SecGen wld assign such rep other <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> activities here as well. (Signed
                                Beam).<note n="2" xml:id="d356fn2">In telegram 1062 (Usgoc 500) to
                                Djakarta, March 31, Ambassador Cochran was informed that if the
                                plans advanced in <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 961 were
                                implemented, the Department of State would concur
                                (357.AA/3–3051).</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Department pass Hague, Brussels, Canberra. Sent Department 1337, repeated info
                    Hague 130, Brussels 2, Canberra 20.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
